<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Sustainable Wardrobe Tips</title>
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css" />
    <% layout('./layouts/boilerplate') -%>
    <style>
      body {
        background: rgb(21,157,179);
        background: -moz-linear-gradient(349deg, rgba(21,157,179,1) 22%, rgba(245,255,222,1) 90%);
        background: -webkit-linear-gradient(349deg, rgba(21,157,179,1) 22%, rgba(245,255,222,1) 90%);
        background: linear-gradient(349deg, rgba(21,157,179,1) 22%, rgba(245,255,222,1) 90%);
        filter: progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.gradient(startColorstr="#159db3",endColorstr="#f5ffde",GradientType=1);
        background-attachment: fixed;
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        padding: 2rem;
      }
      .header {
        background: rgba(92, 208, 152, 0.7); /* Make the background semi-transparent */
        backdrop-filter: blur(5px); /* Apply backdrop filter for a blur effect */
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 3rem;
        padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;
        border-radius: 20px;
        color: #091a13c7;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        font-weight: bold;
        animation: fadeIn 2s ease-in-out;
        margin-top: 20px;
        z-index: 2;
      }
      .tips-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 2rem;
        animation: fadeInUp 1s ease-in-out;
      }
      .tip-container {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); /* Make the background semi-transparent */
        backdrop-filter: blur(5px); /* Apply backdrop filter for a blur effect */
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0px 0px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        transition: transform 0.4s ease;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .tip-container:hover {
        transform: scale(1.05);
      }
      .tip-icon {
        font-size: 3rem;
        color: #004d40;
        position: absolute;
        top: -20px;
        right: -20px;
        opacity: 0.1;
      }
      .tip-title {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: #1b2b29d4;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-weight: bold;
        position: relative;
      }
      .tip-text {
        font-size: 1rem;
        color: #0e8d6f;
      }
      .call-to-action {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 3rem;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #74fdffe4;
        animation: fadeInUp 1.5s ease-in-out;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .call-to-action a {
        color: rgba(247, 252, 252, 0.855);
        text-decoration: underline;
        transition: color 0.25s;
      }
      .call-to-action a:hover {
        color: rgba(35, 216, 216, 0.855);
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
      @keyframes fadeIn {
        from {
          opacity: 0;
        }
        to {
          opacity: 1;
        }
      }
      @keyframes fadeInUp {
        from {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: translateY(30px);
        }
        to {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateY(0);
        }
      }
      @media (max-width: 996px ) {
        .tips-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="header">Sustainable Wardrobe Tips</div>

    <div class="container tips-grid">
      <!-- Tip 1 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-leaf tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">1. Buy Less, Choose Well</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Focus on buying quality over quantity. Choosing well-made, timeless
          pieces reduces waste and ensures your wardrobe is built to last.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 2 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-recycle tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">2. Embrace Second-Hand</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Thrift shopping helps you find unique pieces while reducing the demand
          for fast fashion. Vintage shops and second-hand platforms are great
          alternatives to buying new.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 3 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-tools tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">3. Repair and Upcycle</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Learn simple repair techniques to prolong the life of your clothes, or
          get creative by upcycling old garments into something new.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 4 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-tshirt tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">4. Proper Clothing Care</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Washing your clothes less often and at lower temperatures helps reduce
          wear and tear. Air-drying instead of tumble drying also saves energy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 5 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-fabric tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">5. Opt for Sustainable Fabrics</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Choose fabrics like organic cotton, hemp, and recycled polyester, which
          have a smaller environmental footprint compared to conventional materials.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 6 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-gift tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">6. Donate or Recycle Clothes</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Instead of throwing away old clothes, donate them to charity or recycle
          them through textile recycling programs to reduce waste.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 7 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-handshake tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">7. Swap Clothes with Friends</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Organize clothing swaps with friends or at local events to refresh your
          wardrobe without buying anything new. Itâ€™s sustainable and fun!
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 8 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-heart tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">8. Support Ethical Brands</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Buy from brands that prioritize sustainability, ethical practices, and
          fair wages for workers to ensure your purchases align with eco-friendly
          values.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tip 9 -->
      <div class="tip-container">
        <i class="fas fa-briefcase tip-icon"></i>
        <div class="tip-title">9. Build a Capsule Wardrobe</div>
        <p class="tip-text">
          Minimize your wardrobe to versatile, essential pieces that work well
          together. This reduces the need for unnecessary purchases and promotes
          mindful consumption.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Call to action -->
    <div class="call-to-action">
      Ready to make your wardrobe more sustainable? <br />
      <a href="/">Go to Home</a> to make sustainable wardrobe.
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
